chapter.sect1:
DNS Management
The following tables list the minimum DNS requirements to run &productname;, using example.com as the example domain. Your DNS management is platform-dependent, for example Microsoft AKS assigns IP addresses to your services, which you will map to A records. Amazon EKS assigns host names, which you will use to create CNAMEs. &suse; &caasp; provides the flexibility to manage your name services in nearly any way you wish. The chapters for each platform in this guide provide the relevant DNS instructions.
